BIRNIN KEBBI – The local branch of the academic staff union of universities ASUU Kebbi state has formally joined the nationwide month-long warning strike declared by the national body of the union on Monday. The decision to comply with the directive of the mother union was reached on Monday after the state branch of ASUU federal university Birnin Kebbi held its meeting by 2 pm and resolved unanimously to join the strike, Dr. Abbass Yusuf Bazata the Kebbi branch president disclosed that “we don’t have local demands except those our mother union are pursuing, so we have formally joined the month-long warning strike all academic activities are hereby halted till further notice or pending another directive from the National body. Dr. Bazata enjoined all academic staff to comply by keeping away from lecture halls and/or any other academic activities, he appeal to students and parents to show understanding as ASUU is battling for their sake to rescue public Nigerian universities.